<p>I'm an Australian software engineer based in London. I work at <a href="https://www.co2ai.com/">CO2 AI</a> on the Supplier Web team, building tools that help large companies measure and cut their carbon emissions.</p>

<p>Most of what I think about these days is how our day-to-day work is changing now that we build software with AI. Over the last year I've helped my team go from a couple of us experimenting with coding agents to most of the team using them every day — running the training, building some of our internal tooling, and having a lot of the "okay, but how do we actually do this well?" conversations.</p>

<p>I don't think anyone has this figured out yet, and when someone tells me they've got the perfect workflow I usually take it as a sign they're underrating how fast it's all still changing. So I try to stay close to the people doing the most interesting work, work out what actually holds up, and bring my team along with me.</p>

<p>Outside of that, I'm a big music fan — you can see what I listen to on my <a href="https://last.fm/user/harryludson">Last.fm profile</a> or my <a href="https://bandcamp.com/harryludson">Bandcamp collection</a>. There's more of what I'm building on <a href="https://github.com/larryhudson">GitHub</a>.</p>

<p>This site is where I think out loud: what I'm reading, what I'm building, and what I'm thinking. The latest is below.</p>

